00:29:19,861 --> 00:29:23,862
to this, two two-set blocks a year,

577
00:29:24,682 --> 00:29:26,202
each with its own creative.

578
00:29:27,042 --> 00:29:30,903
So what that meant was our inflexible need,

579
00:29:31,043 --> 00:29:33,684
which was only one incredible world guide

580
00:29:34,044 --> 00:29:36,124
to populate hundreds and hundreds of cards

581
00:29:36,364 --> 00:29:40,465
with world-class assets, turned into two of those.

582
00:29:40,765 --> 00:29:41,906
We needed to do it twice.

583
00:29:43,086 --> 00:29:46,947
Without sacrificing quality, we don't just get more time.

584
00:29:47,707 --> 00:29:49,287
We don't get to double our head count.

585
00:29:50,563 --> 00:29:54,990
And we had to figure out how to accomplish this and how to accomplish it sustainably.

586
00:29:57,073 --> 00:29:59,777
And so our new flexible solution was...

587
00:30:01,076 --> 00:30:03,298
our old flexible solution, we just do it twice.

588
00:30:03,578 --> 00:30:05,479
It's a flexible solution, it's scalable.

589
00:30:05,820 --> 00:30:08,982
Like all of those learnings that allowed us to do it once

