00:30:09,463 --> 00:30:11,144
and how much is healthy to front load,

591
00:30:11,164 --> 00:30:12,626
how our organization should work,

592
00:30:13,466 --> 00:30:17,330
how we avoid a culture of handoffs,

593
00:30:17,970 --> 00:30:19,972
all of those things work, it scales.

594
00:30:20,232 --> 00:30:21,693
We just have to take ownership of it.

595
00:30:24,181 --> 00:30:25,682
it did create a new problem.

596
00:30:25,903 --> 00:30:28,044
This cleanup and finalization phase,

597
00:30:28,485 --> 00:30:29,986
we used to have months to do it.

598
00:30:30,807 --> 00:30:33,269
And our concept artists no longer had that luxury.

599
00:30:33,649 --> 00:30:35,391
And so we needed to find a new way

600
00:30:35,751 --> 00:30:38,614
to get to a hard stop faster so that we could start

601
00:30:38,734 --> 00:30:42,257
front loading that healthy work for the next push.

602
00:30:43,138 --> 00:30:48,343
And so in order to do that, our concept is still scalable.

603
00:30:48,383 --> 00:30:49,303
We just did it more.

604
00:30:50,172 --> 00:30:59,038
So we have a small push after the push prime where three artists come in for another three

605
00:30:59,078 --> 00:31:01,420
weeks and help us get to that hard stop.

606
00:31:01,980 --> 00:31:06,543
This has led us to further customize who we invite in and when.

