00:31:07,264 --> 00:31:13,228
As an example, we bring in more international talent for that primary push and we have learned

608
00:31:13,268 --> 00:31:19,292
that a really great thing to do for that follow-up push is bring in more local artists.

609
00:31:19,652 --> 00:31:24,236
We have a lot of our illustrators, several of them, are local to the Seattle area.

610
00:31:24,376 --> 00:31:27,138
They've been working with us for years and they're able to come in.

611
00:31:27,178 --> 00:31:31,781
They understand that it's a different challenge, that the challenge is to clean up and edit

612
00:31:31,881 --> 00:31:33,342
and help us get to that hard stop.

613
00:31:33,962 --> 00:31:36,024
And we have really built that relationship with them

614
00:31:36,404 --> 00:31:38,045
so less communication is needed.

615
00:31:38,365 --> 00:31:39,526
They understand the job.

616
00:31:39,546 --> 00:31:40,787
They understand what they're doing.

617
00:31:41,287 --> 00:31:44,149
And they come in and just take a hatchet to it,

618
00:31:44,509 --> 00:31:45,370
knock it out of the park.

619
00:31:46,491 --> 00:31:49,953
So a flexible solution will scale.

620
00:31:50,874 --> 00:31:52,195
That's literally how we do it.

